WEBVTT

1
00:01:02.087 --> 00:01:06.205
Mr. Bond. Mr. Bond. I'm so glad
I caught you. Your office called.

2
00:01:06.287 --> 00:01:10.200
They're sending a helicopter
to pick you up. Some sort of emergency.

3
00:01:10.287 --> 00:01:13.404
It usually is. Thank you.

4
00:01:13.487 --> 00:01:15.876
<i>(helicopter approaches)</i>

5
00:02:14.487 --> 00:02:15.966
<i>(screams)</i>

6
00:02:28.567 --> 00:02:31.320
<i>(man laughing)</i>

7
00:02:32.167 --> 00:02:34.556
<i>(man) Good afternoon. Mr. Bond.</i>

8
00:02:34.647 --> 00:02:39.323
<i>Don't concern yourself with the pilot.
One of my less useful people.</i>

9
00:02:44.647 --> 00:02:48.083
<i>You are now flying
Remote Control Airways.</i>

10
00:02:48.167 --> 00:02:50.203
<i>(man laughs)</i>

11
00:03:15.607 --> 00:03:18.917
<i>Think twice. 007. It's a long way down.</i>

12
00:03:47.807 --> 00:03:50.367
<i>(man laughs loudly)</i>

13
00:03:53.207 --> 00:03:56.961
<i>I've looked forward
to this moment. Mr. Bond.</i>

14
00:03:57.047 --> 00:04:00.323
<i>I intend to enjoy it to the full.</i>

15
00:04:14.047 --> 00:04:16.356
<i>(man laughs hysterically)</i>

16
00:04:36.167 --> 00:04:39.762
<i>Really. have you no respect for the dead?</i>

17
00:04:41.367 --> 00:04:43.562
<i>Goodbye. Mr. Bond.</i>

18
00:04:43.647 --> 00:04:46.639
<i>I trust you had a pleasant... fright?</i>

19
00:05:04.367 --> 00:05:10.806
<i>You're fading from my picture. Mr. Bond.
but the end cannot be far away.</i>

20
00:05:10.887 --> 00:05:13.276
<i>(laughs wildly)</i>

21
00:05:43.287 --> 00:05:46.085
Mr. Bond! Mr. Bond!

22
00:05:49.567 --> 00:05:51.558
We can do a deal.

23
00:05:51.647 --> 00:05:56.038
I'll buy you a delicatessen.
In stainless steel.

24
00:05:57.287 --> 00:06:00.438
- Please!
- All right. Keep your hair on.

25
00:06:00.527 --> 00:06:03.519
Put me down. Put me down!

26
00:06:03.607 --> 00:06:05.962
Oh. you want to get off?

27
00:06:08.247 --> 00:06:10.238
Mr. Bond!

28
00:06:12.167 --> 00:06:14.158
<i>(loud crash)</i>

29
00:06:17.247 --> 00:06:20.239
<i># "For Your Eyes Only" by Sheena Easton</i>

30
00:06:33.647 --> 00:06:39.882
<i># For your eyes only
can see me through the night</i>

31
00:06:41.807 --> 00:06:48.121
<i># For your eyes only I never need to hide</i>

32
00:06:50.127 --> 00:06:56.157
<i># You can see so much in me.
so much in me that's new</i>

33
00:06:58.127 --> 00:07:04.839
<i># I never felt until I looked at you</i>

34
00:07:04.927 --> 00:07:09.159
<i># For your eyes only</i>

35
00:07:09.247 --> 00:07:11.761
<i># Only for you</i>

36
00:07:11.847 --> 00:07:16.602
<i># You'll see what no one else can see
and now I'm breaking free</i>

37
00:07:16.687 --> 00:07:20.077
<i># For your eyes only</i>

38
00:07:20.167 --> 00:07:22.761
<i># Only for you</i>

39
00:07:22.847 --> 00:07:25.725
<i># The love I know you need in me</i>

40
00:07:25.807 --> 00:07:28.446
<i># The fantasy you've freed in me</i>

41
00:07:28.527 --> 00:07:32.281
<i># Only for you</i>

42
00:07:32.487 --> 00:07:35.957
<i># Only for you</i>

43
00:07:44.527 --> 00:07:50.523
<i># For your eyes only.
the nights are never cold</i>

44
00:07:52.727 --> 00:07:58.723
<i># You really know me.
that's all I need to know</i>

45
00:08:01.167 --> 00:08:07.163
<i># Maybe I'm an open book
because I know you're mine</i>

46
00:08:09.047 --> 00:08:15.805
<i># But you don't need
to read between the lines</i>

47
00:08:15.887 --> 00:08:20.119
<i># For your eyes only</i>

48
00:08:20.207 --> 00:08:22.641
<i># Only for you</i>

49
00:08:22.727 --> 00:08:27.517
<i># You'll see what no one else can see
and now I'm breaking free</i>

50
00:08:27.607 --> 00:08:30.963
<i># For your eyes only</i>

51
00:08:31.047 --> 00:08:33.720
<i># Only for you</i>

52
00:08:33.807 --> 00:08:36.560
<i># The passions that collide in me</i>

53
00:08:36.647 --> 00:08:39.320
<i># The wild abandoned side of me</i>

54
00:08:39.407 --> 00:08:43.002
<i># Only for you</i>

55
00:08:43.087 --> 00:08:47.239
<i># For your eyes only</i>

56
00:09:46.287 --> 00:09:48.278
<i>(electronic beeping)</i>

57
00:09:51.207 --> 00:09:55.962
- Afternoon. How's it looking topside?
- Beautiful day. Just bringing the nets in.

58
00:09:56.047 --> 00:09:58.277
Fish for supper again.

59
00:10:07.647 --> 00:10:11.925
Decode of Russian satellite data. sir.
on British and American ship positions.

60
00:10:12.007 --> 00:10:14.999
- Verify and advise Admiralty.
- Yes. sir.

61
00:10:16.767 --> 00:10:19.156
- Afternoon. sir.
- Hello. Mac.

62
00:10:20.647 --> 00:10:22.638
My watch.

63
00:10:56.607 --> 00:10:58.404
<i>(speaks in Maltese)</i>

64
00:11:03.647 --> 00:11:04.682
<i>(alarm)</i>

65
00:11:04.767 --> 00:11:07.839
Where the hell did that come from?

66
00:11:07.927 --> 00:11:09.918
<i>(alarm)</i>

67
00:11:11.727 --> 00:11:14.924
- What's going on?
- Unidentified object closing fast.

68
00:11:18.847 --> 00:11:22.362
<i>(shouts in Maltese)</i>

69
00:11:22.447 --> 00:11:24.358
<i>(shouting)</i>

70
00:11:27.927 --> 00:11:30.236
Secure Operations Room!

71
00:11:31.247 --> 00:11:34.045
Destruct ATAC system.

72
00:12:11.047 --> 00:12:12.196
<i>(buzzer)</i>

73
00:12:12.647 --> 00:12:15.081
<i>- Yes?
- First Sea Lord and Vice Admiral.</i>

74
00:12:15.167 --> 00:12:17.442
Send them in.

75
00:12:21.527 --> 00:12:26.362
<i>Shocking news. We've lost our electronic
surveillance ship. the St. Georges.</i>

76
00:12:26.447 --> 00:12:29.484
We had a routine message
at 1600 hours yesterday.

77
00:12:29.567 --> 00:12:32.923
Then nothing. We sighted
floating debris this morning.

78
00:12:33.007 --> 00:12:34.963
My God. Jack.

79
00:12:35.047 --> 00:12:39.404
- How deep is the water there?
- Not deep enough. I'm afraid.

80
00:12:42.327 --> 00:12:44.887
Yes. Comrade Secretary. off Albania.

81
00:12:44.967 --> 00:12:49.438
The suspected British spy ship
which we have been monitoring.

82
00:12:49.527 --> 00:12:55.124
It suggests that there is a chance
of obtaining the ATAC transmitter.

83
00:12:56.567 --> 00:12:59.923
Of course. Comrade.
There will be no direct involvement.

84
00:13:00.007 --> 00:13:07.482
But if it comes on the market we should
not lose such a remarkable opportunity.

85
00:13:07.567 --> 00:13:13.563
<i>With that in mind. I've already
contacted our usual friend in Greece. Da.</i>

86
00:13:40.647 --> 00:13:43.320
<i>(plane approaches)</i>

87
00:14:00.007 --> 00:14:03.363
<i>- Down you go. Go on.
- (parrot) Down you go.</i>

88
00:14:10.167 --> 00:14:15.161
<i>- (parrot) Give us a kiss. Give us a kiss.
- I'll give you a nut. Here you are.</i>

89
00:14:19.807 --> 00:14:21.877
Come on.

90
00:14:21.967 --> 00:14:24.879
- Your packages. señorita.
- Oh. thank you.

91
00:14:26.167 --> 00:14:28.556
<i>(woman speaks in Greek)</i>

92
00:14:29.207 --> 00:14:30.959
<i>(man) Melina!</i>

93
00:14:43.447 --> 00:14:46.883
<i>(they speak in Greek)</i>

94
00:14:46.967 --> 00:14:51.006
- Thank you. darling.
- Hello. Daddy.

95
00:14:51.087 --> 00:14:53.396
Welcome home. Melina.
You look beautiful.

96
00:14:53.487 --> 00:14:57.002
- Thank you.
- Your call from Athens was a surprise.

97
00:14:57.087 --> 00:15:00.443
I was lucky to find you.
You left Crete so suddenly.

98
00:15:01.007 --> 00:15:05.125
Yes. I wanted to come back here and start
work on the temple. You between jobs?

99
00:15:05.207 --> 00:15:08.324
Only for a few days.
I'll lend a hand. if you want.

100
00:15:08.407 --> 00:15:11.285
Darling. it's beautiful. Thank you.

101
00:15:11.367 --> 00:15:14.165
That's for you. And pistachios for Max.

102
00:16:31.047 --> 00:16:35.165
- James.
- Moneypenny. a feast for my eyes.

103
00:16:35.247 --> 00:16:39.684
- What about the rest of you?
- Well. I was going to get around to that.

104
00:16:39.767 --> 00:16:42.122
Well. you'd better go in. M's on leave.

105
00:16:42.207 --> 00:16:46.325
The minister's here with the chief of staff
and wants to see you immediately.

106
00:16:46.407 --> 00:16:49.558
- I'll be right back.
- I can hardly wait.

107
00:16:49.647 --> 00:16:53.276
Haven't you forgotten something?

108
00:16:53.367 --> 00:16:55.358
As M's away.

109
00:17:00.167 --> 00:17:03.125
- Ah. there you are. 007.
- Hm.

110
00:17:03.207 --> 00:17:05.038
Minister. Chief of Staff.

111
00:17:05.127 --> 00:17:07.687
Are you aware of our ATAC system. 007?

112
00:17:07.767 --> 00:17:11.237
ATAC. sir. Automatic Targeting
Attack Communicator.

113
00:17:11.327 --> 00:17:16.401
Uses an ultra-low frequency transmitter to
order our submarines to launch missiles.

114
00:17:16.487 --> 00:17:21.197
<i>Five days ago. our spy ship St. Georges
was sunk in the Ionian Sea.</i>

115
00:17:21.287 --> 00:17:25.644
She was equipped with ATAC. If that
transmitter fell into the wrong hands.

116
00:17:25.727 --> 00:17:29.436
it would render
our entire Polaris fleet useless.

117
00:17:29.527 --> 00:17:32.246
- Every order could be countermanded.
- Worse.

118
00:17:32.327 --> 00:17:37.162
Our own submarines could be ordered
to attack our own cities.

119
00:17:37.247 --> 00:17:39.681
Have we begun a salvage operation?

120
00:17:39.767 --> 00:17:42.076
An official operation was impossible.

121
00:17:42.167 --> 00:17:44.727
<i>The St. Georges
was off the Albanian coast.</i>

122
00:17:44.807 --> 00:17:48.595
We asked Sir Timothy Havelock.
the archeologist. to locate the wreck.

123
00:17:48.687 --> 00:17:54.284
Before he could report. he and his wife
were killed by a hit man. Hector Gonzales.

124
00:17:54.367 --> 00:17:57.916
The Greek police were able
to identify Gonzales from a description

125
00:17:58.007 --> 00:18:01.761
given to them by Melina.
Sir Havelock's daughter.

126
00:18:01.847 --> 00:18:04.805
Operation Undertow -
the information's all here.

127
00:18:04.887 --> 00:18:07.526
Now. Gonzales is at a villa near Madrid.

128
00:18:07.607 --> 00:18:12.476
Isolate him and apply the necessary
pressure to find out who hired him.

129
00:19:05.487 --> 00:19:07.478
<i>(distant dance music)</i>

130
00:19:39.127 --> 00:19:41.118
<i>(dance music)</i>

131
00:20:18.087 --> 00:20:20.078
<i>(branch snaps)</i>

132
00:20:36.047 --> 00:20:38.880
A Walther PPK.

133
00:20:38.967 --> 00:20:42.039
Standard issue. British Secret Service.

134
00:20:42.127 --> 00:20:44.561
Licensed to kill...

135
00:20:45.847 --> 00:20:47.838
or be killed.

136
00:20:47.927 --> 00:20:49.997
Take him away.

137
00:20:59.567 --> 00:21:01.444
<i>(sound of arrow)</i>

138
00:21:08.207 --> 00:21:10.641
<i>(screaming)</i>

139
00:21:16.887 --> 00:21:18.923
Excuse me.

140
00:21:36.687 --> 00:21:39.599
<i>Vamos. rápido.
que no se puede escapar. Corred.</i>

141
00:21:48.967 --> 00:21:51.322
<i>Lo tenemos ahora. cógelo.</i>

142
00:22:00.087 --> 00:22:01.839
<i>(man)...por aquí.</i>

143
00:22:01.927 --> 00:22:04.157
You've outstayed your welcome.
Come on.

144
00:22:12.047 --> 00:22:14.481
<i>(man) Ése no se puede escapar.</i>

145
00:22:14.927 --> 00:22:17.919
<i>No importa. Sigue. sigue. sigue.</i>

146
00:22:18.007 --> 00:22:19.326
<i>Que se nos escapa.</i>

147
00:22:32.687 --> 00:22:36.839
- Well. I hope you have a car.
- This way.

148
00:22:54.807 --> 00:22:56.798
Hurry.

149
00:23:08.247 --> 00:23:10.807
- Who are you?
- He killed my parents.

150
00:23:10.887 --> 00:23:13.321
The Havelocks?

151
00:23:13.407 --> 00:23:15.796
I'm sorry.

152
00:23:20.487 --> 00:23:24.196
- How did you know where Gonzales was?
- Through a detective agency.

153
00:23:24.287 --> 00:23:27.165
<i>- What were you doing there?
- (tires screech)</i>

154
00:23:27.247 --> 00:23:29.636
I'm afraid we're being out-horsepowered.

155
00:23:44.567 --> 00:23:45.841
Excuse me.

156
00:23:58.127 --> 00:23:59.765
Take the low road.

157
00:24:01.647 --> 00:24:04.002
Not that low.

158
00:24:04.287 --> 00:24:06.801
<i>(horn)</i>

159
00:24:16.647 --> 00:24:19.639
You don't mind if I drive. do you?

160
00:24:29.847 --> 00:24:31.838
<i>(engine fails to start)</i>

161
00:24:34.047 --> 00:24:36.117
<i>Por favor. empujen.</i>

162
00:24:39.727 --> 00:24:41.718
<i>(engine starts)</i>

163
00:25:32.687 --> 00:25:35.804
- Go backwards forwards quickly.
- Hm?

164
00:26:35.487 --> 00:26:37.876
Love a drive in the country. don't you?

165
00:26:44.487 --> 00:26:45.840
Hold tight.

166
00:27:10.367 --> 00:27:13.165
We haven't been
properly introduced. Melina.

167
00:27:13.247 --> 00:27:16.478
My name is Bond... James Bond.

168
00:27:19.127 --> 00:27:21.163
<i>Muchas gracias.</i>

169
00:27:22.487 --> 00:27:25.479
Olympic has a flight at 11.

170
00:27:27.767 --> 00:27:31.555
It should be safe to go to the airport now.

171
00:27:35.527 --> 00:27:38.803
- Are you all right?
- I'm fine.

172
00:27:38.887 --> 00:27:40.798
Really.

173
00:27:40.887 --> 00:27:44.880
- Going back to your father's ship?
- Yes. I'm continuing his work.

174
00:27:44.967 --> 00:27:47.959
- But this business is unfinished.
- What business?

175
00:27:48.047 --> 00:27:51.084
The man who paid Gonzales.

176
00:27:51.167 --> 00:27:53.681
The Chinese have a saying.

177
00:27:53.767 --> 00:27:58.443
"Before setting out on revenge.
you first dig two graves."

178
00:27:58.527 --> 00:28:04.762
I don't expect you to understand.
You're English. but I'm half-Greek.

179
00:28:04.847 --> 00:28:10.956
And Greek women. like Elektra.
always avenge their loved ones.

180
00:28:11.047 --> 00:28:13.242
I must go.

181
00:28:19.127 --> 00:28:23.439
You were meant to question Gonzales.
not let Miss Havelock perforate him.

182
00:28:23.527 --> 00:28:24.960
I quite agree.

183
00:28:25.047 --> 00:28:29.006
We'll have to tell the prime minister
Operation Undertow is dead.

184
00:28:29.087 --> 00:28:31.726
She'll have our guts for garters.

185
00:28:31.807 --> 00:28:35.595
If you care to look again
at page 2 paragraph 4 of my report. sir.

186
00:28:35.687 --> 00:28:38.724
you will note that I saw someone
paying off Gonzales.

187
00:28:38.807 --> 00:28:43.323
Assuming that that was for Havelock's
murder. there is still a glimmer of hope.

188
00:28:43.407 --> 00:28:47.320
- I don't follow.
- If we could identify that someone...

189
00:28:47.407 --> 00:28:50.240
- Why don't you try the Identigraph?
- Hm.

190
00:28:51.487 --> 00:28:53.796
- Yes. sir.
- Well. get cracking. 007.

191
00:28:53.887 --> 00:28:55.445
Hm.

192
00:28:55.527 --> 00:28:57.006
Minister.

193
00:29:00.687 --> 00:29:02.484
Hello. Q.

194
00:29:02.567 --> 00:29:07.118
- Smithers. how's the arm?
- Coming along very nicely. thank you. sir.

195
00:29:08.127 --> 00:29:10.083
That'll come in handy.

196
00:29:10.167 --> 00:29:13.045
- What are you doing here. 007?
- Identigraph. Q.

197
00:29:13.127 --> 00:29:15.118
This way.

198
00:29:24.807 --> 00:29:29.358
- Stinging in the rain?
- That's not funny. 007.

199
00:29:29.447 --> 00:29:32.007
I see you got the Lotus
back together again.

200
00:29:32.087 --> 00:29:36.000
I disregard these gibes
about our equipment. 007.

201
00:29:36.087 --> 00:29:40.558
- I bet you don't find it funny in the field.
- Indeed. I don't.

202
00:29:45.527 --> 00:29:50.123
This 3-D visual Identigraph
is still in the experimental stage.

203
00:29:50.207 --> 00:29:52.880
Now. once we get
a composite of the man.

204
00:29:52.967 --> 00:29:57.597
we can find a match by patching into the
photographic files of the Sûreté. Interpol.

205
00:29:57.687 --> 00:29:59.996
CIA. the Mossad...

206
00:30:00.087 --> 00:30:05.605
And the West German Police. Yes.
you've told me so already. Q. five times.

207
00:30:05.687 --> 00:30:07.678
Thank you. 007.

208
00:30:08.647 --> 00:30:11.081
Right.

209
00:30:11.167 --> 00:30:15.206
Describe the person you wish to identify
and I'll program the information.

210
00:30:15.287 --> 00:30:19.075
Male Caucasian. Late 30s.

211
00:30:20.447 --> 00:30:23.644
Hair - fine. light brown.

212
00:30:26.087 --> 00:30:28.157
That's it. Parted in the middle.

213
00:30:28.247 --> 00:30:30.317
Wait a minute.

214
00:30:30.407 --> 00:30:31.396
Right.

215
00:30:31.487 --> 00:30:34.923
<i>- (Bond) Eyes - a little smaller.
- Uh-huh.</i>

216
00:30:35.007 --> 00:30:38.682
Blue. A little greyer.

217
00:30:38.767 --> 00:30:41.600
That's it. you have it. Now. nose.

218
00:30:43.887 --> 00:30:46.924
- A nose. not a banana. Q.
- Sorry.

219
00:30:47.567 --> 00:30:50.400
Stop. Lips fuller.

220
00:30:50.487 --> 00:30:52.796
<i>(Q) Uh-huh. Whoops.</i>

221
00:30:54.207 --> 00:30:56.357
- No. no. no. Mouth wider.
- Uh-huh.

222
00:30:56.447 --> 00:30:58.438
Good.

223
00:31:01.367 --> 00:31:03.597
Thank you.

224
00:31:03.687 --> 00:31:06.679
Thank you. Sharon.
You can go. I'll lock up.

225
00:31:06.767 --> 00:31:08.723
OK.

226
00:31:09.727 --> 00:31:13.322
I reckon we're almost there. Q.
Apart from glasses.

227
00:31:13.407 --> 00:31:16.001
- Steel-rimmed.
- Yeah.

228
00:31:16.087 --> 00:31:18.647
- Octagonal.
- Octagonal.

229
00:31:21.087 --> 00:31:23.760
That's him. That's our man.

230
00:31:24.407 --> 00:31:27.001
Right. I'll try and get a match.

231
00:31:40.447 --> 00:31:42.517
<i>- (buzzer)
- Yes?</i>

232
00:31:42.607 --> 00:31:45.326
Ah. sir. the man we want
is Emile Leopold Locque.

233
00:31:45.407 --> 00:31:47.841
<i>An enforcer in the Brussels underworld.</i>

234
00:31:47.927 --> 00:31:51.397
He's been convicted
of several particularly brutal murders.

235
00:31:51.527 --> 00:31:55.805
He escaped from Namur prison
by strangling his psychiatrist.

236
00:31:55.887 --> 00:31:59.277
He has worked for drug syndicates
in Marseilles and Hong Kong.

237
00:31:59.367 --> 00:32:01.756
Now reported working
for Greek smugglers.

238
00:32:01.847 --> 00:32:05.965
The Italian Secret Service think
that he is at this moment in Cortina.

239
00:32:06.047 --> 00:32:10.120
I'll instruct Ferrara. our man in
Northern Italy. to contact you there.

240
00:32:10.207 --> 00:32:13.358
And. 007. try not to muck it up again.

241
00:32:14.087 --> 00:32:15.964
I'll do my best. sir.

242
00:32:16.047 --> 00:32:18.515
I'll leave you to lock up.
Let me out. will you?

243
00:33:00.567 --> 00:33:02.762
<i>- Grazie.
- Prego. signore.</i>

244
00:33:52.767 --> 00:33:55.520
The snow this year is better at Innsbruck.

245
00:33:55.607 --> 00:33:58.075
But not at St. Moritz.

246
00:33:58.167 --> 00:34:01.921
- Ferrara.
- Bond. James.

247
00:34:02.007 --> 00:34:03.406
Luigi.

248
00:34:03.487 --> 00:34:06.285
I presume London's briefed you?

249
00:34:06.367 --> 00:34:09.677
If Locque's in Cortina. we'll find him.

250
00:34:09.767 --> 00:34:13.442
I have a reliable Greek contact here.
An Anglophile.

251
00:34:13.527 --> 00:34:16.246
He helped us out last year
on a smuggling operation.

252
00:34:16.327 --> 00:34:19.717
- Then what's he doing in Cortina?
- He...

253
00:34:23.927 --> 00:34:26.885
...spends a few months a year
here at his chalet.

254
00:34:26.967 --> 00:34:30.755
He's in shipping. insurance.
oil exploration.

255
00:34:30.847 --> 00:34:34.601
Knows everything going on. Very reliable.

256
00:34:34.687 --> 00:34:38.316
The British gave him a medal
for resistance fighting during the war.

257
00:34:38.407 --> 00:34:41.524
- Yes. but can I meet him?
- I've set it up.

258
00:34:41.607 --> 00:34:44.246
He is waiting for us
at the Olympic ice rink.

259
00:34:47.567 --> 00:34:51.401
Good! Extend your arms.

260
00:34:51.487 --> 00:34:53.478
<i>(applause)</i>

261
00:35:00.687 --> 00:35:03.155
- Signor Kristatos?
- Ah.

262
00:35:04.887 --> 00:35:07.606
- Kristatos. Aris Kristatos.
- Bond. James Bond.

263
00:35:07.687 --> 00:35:12.841
- Would you join me in some gluhwein?
- That's a very good idea. Thank you.

264
00:35:12.927 --> 00:35:16.556
Well. gentlemen. how can I help you?

265
00:35:16.647 --> 00:35:19.115
We'd like some information.

266
00:35:26.327 --> 00:35:29.683
My protégée.
A sure winner in the next Olympics.

267
00:35:29.767 --> 00:35:34.318
She's completely absorbed in her skating.
but innocent in the ways of the world.

268
00:35:35.007 --> 00:35:39.523
The day she wins the gold medal
will be the greatest in my life.

269
00:35:46.087 --> 00:35:48.123
<i>(Kristatos) Bibi!</i>

270
00:35:48.207 --> 00:35:52.723
Here are some new admirers for you.
Mr. Bond. Mr. Ferrara - Bibi Dahl.

271
00:35:52.807 --> 00:35:56.720
And her coach. Jacoba Brink.
Once a world-class skater herself.

272
00:35:56.807 --> 00:36:01.358
I've seen Miss Brink skate. The world will
soon see much of your skating. Miss Dahl.

273
00:36:01.447 --> 00:36:04.200
Only if she works harder - much harder.

274
00:36:04.287 --> 00:36:09.486
- Uncle Ari. can't I stop now? I'm pooped.
- That's for Miss Brink to decide.

275
00:36:09.567 --> 00:36:12.365
Come. Bibi. Another half-hour of practice.

276
00:36:12.447 --> 00:36:17.567
- Will you take me to the biathlon?
- You know I have to work this afternoon.

277
00:36:20.327 --> 00:36:23.603
Bibi wants to know if you
would escort her. Mr. Bond.

278
00:36:23.687 --> 00:36:27.077
- I don't think...
- I would feel better if you were with her.

279
00:36:29.647 --> 00:36:32.605
Well. I'd be delighted.
I'm staying at the Miramonte.

280
00:36:32.687 --> 00:36:34.279
Great!

281
00:36:35.087 --> 00:36:38.204
Now. how can I help you?

282
00:36:38.287 --> 00:36:42.599
- Do you know this man?
- Yes. Locque. Columbo's right hand.

283
00:36:42.687 --> 00:36:47.602
Milos Columbo. His name came up
in connection with a smuggling operation.

284
00:36:47.687 --> 00:36:52.556
That's the least of his offenses.
Drugs. white slavery. contract murder.

285
00:36:52.647 --> 00:36:57.641
In the Greek underworld. he is
known as "The Dove". A very sick joke.

286
00:36:57.727 --> 00:37:00.605
- Where is this "Dove"?
- In Greece. I would guess.

287
00:37:00.687 --> 00:37:03.565
Once we were like brothers.
Now he hates me.

288
00:37:03.647 --> 00:37:08.482
We fought together in the Greek
Resistance and against the Communists.

289
00:37:08.567 --> 00:37:12.037
After that. he took a different path.

290
00:37:14.007 --> 00:37:16.680
Well. thank you
for your time. Mr. Kristatos.

291
00:37:16.767 --> 00:37:22.763
My pleasure. I leave for Corfu soon. If I get
any more information. I will call Ferrara.

292
00:37:32.327 --> 00:37:37.242
What do you think? Does this "Dove".
have the resources to mount a salvage?

293
00:37:37.327 --> 00:37:41.923
Definitely. He runs a fleet
of intercoastal freighters in the Aegean.

294
00:37:42.007 --> 00:37:45.079
I'll ring my office in Milano.
They may have more on him.

295
00:37:54.647 --> 00:37:58.435
- Luigi. I'll see you later.
- OK.

296
00:38:12.287 --> 00:38:15.597
<i>- Is this the one you mean. signora?
- (woman) I'll take it.</i>

297
00:38:15.687 --> 00:38:18.520
Deliver it to the Hotel Cristallo. please.

298
00:38:26.687 --> 00:38:29.485
Oh! Beg your pardon.

299
00:38:30.487 --> 00:38:32.955
<i>Buongiorno. May I help you?</i>

300
00:38:33.047 --> 00:38:35.402
Yes. Give me a dozen lilies. will you?

301
00:38:42.207 --> 00:38:44.437
I'll pick them up later.

302
00:38:51.007 --> 00:38:52.998
Come on. quickly.

303
00:39:08.607 --> 00:39:11.599
Send them to the funeral. will you?

304
00:39:15.287 --> 00:39:19.075
Slow down. Would you mind telling me
what you're doing in Cortina?

305
00:39:19.167 --> 00:39:22.364
- Your telegram.
- What telegram?

306
00:39:22.447 --> 00:39:25.598
It said you found the man
and to meet you here today.

307
00:39:25.687 --> 00:39:29.077
I didn't send a telegram. Now. get in.

308
00:39:30.767 --> 00:39:32.883
The station. please.

309
00:39:32.967 --> 00:39:36.403
- Are we leaving?
- Not "we". you. And now.

310
00:39:36.487 --> 00:39:38.796
You don't tell me what to do.

311
00:39:38.887 --> 00:39:41.560
<i>- La stazione. per favore.
- Si. signore.</i>

312
00:39:44.567 --> 00:39:46.558
<i>(siren)</i>

313
00:39:54.968 --> 00:39:58.005
Did you find the man
who hired Gonzales?

314
00:39:58.088 --> 00:39:59.999
I'm working on it.

315
00:40:00.088 --> 00:40:04.286
He's here. isn't he?
That's why you're here.

316
00:40:04.368 --> 00:40:07.405
<i>- Driver. stop. Go back.
- Vai avanti.</i>

317
00:40:07.488 --> 00:40:10.400
- I'm staying.
- So you can put an arrow in his back?

318
00:40:10.488 --> 00:40:13.400
You do that and we'll never find out
who is behind this.

319
00:40:13.488 --> 00:40:17.117
It was my parents they killed. not yours.
Let me out. Driver. stop.

320
00:40:17.208 --> 00:40:18.926
<i>Vai avanti.</i>

321
00:40:19.008 --> 00:40:20.885
<i>Presto.</i>

322
00:40:20.968 --> 00:40:25.086
Melina. look at me. You were lucky once
but they are on to you now.

323
00:40:25.168 --> 00:40:28.205
The telegram.
the motorcycles. they prove it.

324
00:40:28.288 --> 00:40:31.997
- Please. let me handle this.
- You? How are you involved?

325
00:40:32.088 --> 00:40:35.967
All I can say is it's something
of vital interest to both our countries.

326
00:40:36.048 --> 00:40:38.846
More important than my parents?

327
00:40:40.808 --> 00:40:45.359
Your father was part of it. He thought it
important enough to risk his life.

328
00:40:45.448 --> 00:40:49.123
<i>Now. Melina. please trust me.
Go back to the Triana and wait.</i>

329
00:40:49.208 --> 00:40:52.757
Let me find out what I can here.
then I'll come straight to Corfu.

330
00:40:52.848 --> 00:40:57.524
OK. I'll go back and wait. But not for long.

331
00:40:57.608 --> 00:41:00.076
It won't be. I swear.

332
00:41:02.928 --> 00:41:05.488
<i>Amore. amore.</i>

333
00:41:18.608 --> 00:41:20.599
<i>(shower running)</i>

334
00:41:46.088 --> 00:41:49.285
Don't they have showers at the ice rink?

335
00:41:49.368 --> 00:41:51.279
How did you get in here?

336
00:41:51.368 --> 00:41:55.077
One of the porters is a fan.
He'll do anything for me.

337
00:41:55.168 --> 00:41:58.205
And I'll do anything for you.

338
00:41:59.288 --> 00:42:02.917
I'm exceedingly flattered. Bibi.
but you're in training.

339
00:42:03.008 --> 00:42:06.717
That's a laugh. Everybody knows
it builds up muscle tone.

340
00:42:06.808 --> 00:42:11.677
You can start building up a little more
muscle tone by putting on your clothes.

341
00:42:14.048 --> 00:42:17.040
Don't you like me?

342
00:42:17.128 --> 00:42:22.919
Why. I think you're wonderful. Bibi. but I
don't think your Uncle Ari would approve.

343
00:42:23.008 --> 00:42:26.000
Him? He thinks I'm still a virgin.

344
00:42:27.568 --> 00:42:32.801
Yes. well. you get your clothes on
and I'll buy you an ice cream.

345
00:42:40.088 --> 00:42:42.761
Ah. Shall we?

346
00:42:47.768 --> 00:42:50.123
Don't you ever come up for air?

347
00:42:50.208 --> 00:42:53.484
That's why I'll get the gold medal.
Breath control.

348
00:42:53.568 --> 00:42:56.560
Yes. well. you can't lose.

349
00:42:59.968 --> 00:43:00.957
<i>(gunshots)</i>

350
00:43:01.048 --> 00:43:05.246
<i>(PA) The leading skiers are now at
the firing range: Wolf Ghul from Austria.</i>

351
00:43:05.328 --> 00:43:09.799
<i>Kerel Behrta from Switzerland.
Wolfgang Blatt from Holland...</i>

352
00:43:12.408 --> 00:43:15.241
<i>(screams in delight)</i>

353
00:43:24.528 --> 00:43:28.521
<i>(PA) And now Eric Kriegler.
last year's East European champion.</i>

354
00:43:28.608 --> 00:43:33.762
<i>He's passing people and coming up on
the West German champion. Hans Wolf.</i>

355
00:43:36.928 --> 00:43:40.125
- There's Eric Kriegler.
- The East German champion?

356
00:43:41.288 --> 00:43:45.327
- Isn't he beautiful?
- You know something. Bibi? You're fickle.

357
00:43:46.488 --> 00:43:48.558
Hey. Eric!

358
00:43:50.208 --> 00:43:53.166
Come on. let's go watch him shoot.

359
00:44:17.088 --> 00:44:19.477
Eric!

360
00:44:19.568 --> 00:44:23.277
Eric. we'll have a drink at the finish.

361
00:44:25.568 --> 00:44:29.641
- Well. Bibi. I'm afraid I have to leave you.
- No. James. stay with me.

362
00:44:29.728 --> 00:44:32.003
I have an appointment.

363
00:44:32.088 --> 00:44:35.319
Will you come and say goodbye
at the practice rink later?

364
00:44:35.408 --> 00:44:37.763
Please. we're going back to Greece soon.

365
00:44:37.848 --> 00:44:41.921
All right. but if I can't make it.
all I can say is don't grow up any more.

366
00:44:42.008 --> 00:44:46.240
- Huh?
- The opposite sex would never survive it.

367
00:47:57.328 --> 00:47:59.319
<i>Libero.</i>

368
00:48:42.608 --> 00:48:44.599
<i>Libero.</i>

369
00:49:05.528 --> 00:49:07.325
<i>Libero.</i>

370
00:49:18.128 --> 00:49:20.767
<i>- Ehi tu. dov'è il casco?
- Guarda.</i>

371
00:49:26.968 --> 00:49:28.640
<i>Guardia. c'è un pazzo qua.</i>

372
00:51:44.568 --> 00:51:46.001
<i>(gunfire)</i>

373
00:53:30.808 --> 00:53:33.686
It won't take long.
Don't play with the switches.

374
00:53:33.768 --> 00:53:35.565
Right.

375
00:53:47.888 --> 00:53:49.526
James!

376
00:53:49.608 --> 00:53:53.760
- James. what took you so long?
- Well. I took the scenic route.

377
00:53:54.888 --> 00:53:57.846
Tell me more about
your boyfriend. Eric Kriegler.

378
00:53:57.928 --> 00:54:03.127
He doesn't smoke. he only eats health
foods and he won't even talk to girls.

379
00:54:03.208 --> 00:54:06.518
- James. you're jealous.
- Of course.

380
00:54:06.608 --> 00:54:10.396
What else can you tell me about
my rival for your affections?

381
00:54:10.488 --> 00:54:13.127
They say he's a defector
from East Germany.

382
00:54:13.208 --> 00:54:16.359
Bibi! It is time for your rubdown.

383
00:54:25.248 --> 00:54:27.842
I could eat you up alive.

384
00:54:30.648 --> 00:54:34.038
Farewell. Mr. Bond. but not goodbye.

385
00:55:12.448 --> 00:55:14.200
<i>(hooter)</i>

386
00:55:21.368 --> 00:55:23.199
<i>(hooter goes twice)</i>

387
00:55:29.808 --> 00:55:32.276
<i>(hooter goes six times)</i>

388
00:56:11.405 --> 00:56:15.637
I'll be finished around six. Mikes.
Meet me here.

389
00:56:15.725 --> 00:56:18.637
James. how did you know I was here?

390
00:56:18.765 --> 00:56:21.882
<i>I radiotelephoned the Triana.
They said you were coming ashore.</i>

391
00:56:21.965 --> 00:56:26.038
I have to go shopping for the crew. Why
don't you come with me and we can talk?

392
00:56:35.485 --> 00:56:37.282
<i>Yassou.</i>

393
00:56:39.765 --> 00:56:41.756
<i>(they talk in Greek)</i>

394
00:56:49.565 --> 00:56:51.362
<i>Parakalo.</i>

395
00:56:55.845 --> 00:56:58.518
I think you may need that.

396
00:57:23.205 --> 00:57:25.799
My father loved the view from here.

397
00:57:25.885 --> 00:57:29.844
- I can see why.
- We came here often.

398
00:57:29.925 --> 00:57:31.881
- Is Corfu your home?
- No.

399
00:57:31.965 --> 00:57:34.354
<i>My real home's always been the Triana.</i>

400
00:57:34.445 --> 00:57:39.473
The Greek islands. Turkey. North Africa.
wherever my father's work took us.

401
00:57:41.045 --> 00:57:44.355
Did he leave any notes?
They could help us.

402
00:57:44.445 --> 00:57:47.243
No. I don't think so.

403
00:57:48.245 --> 00:57:50.634
To tell the truth.

404
00:57:50.725 --> 00:57:54.957
I haven't had the courage
to go into his study since...

405
00:57:55.045 --> 00:57:57.036
Try not to think about it now.

406
00:57:57.125 --> 00:58:01.403
I'm meeting a man tonight at the casino
who may give us a lead.

407
00:58:05.805 --> 00:58:09.275
<i>Cinq cent mille banque. monsieur.
Qui fait banco?</i>

408
00:58:11.645 --> 00:58:14.284
<i>Banco. Carte. s'il vous plaît.</i>

409
00:58:23.045 --> 00:58:25.195
<i>- Huit.
- Huit.</i>

410
00:58:26.885 --> 00:58:29.399
<i>Et neuf la banque.</i>

411
00:58:30.925 --> 00:58:33.314
You're perspiring. Bunky.

412
00:58:34.645 --> 00:58:37.443
Good evening. Contessa.

413
00:58:39.085 --> 00:58:41.553
<i>Un million banque. monsieur.
Qui fait banco?</i>

414
00:58:43.285 --> 00:58:45.276
Your Lordship?

415
00:58:47.365 --> 00:58:48.878
Five hundred thousand.

416
00:58:48.965 --> 00:58:52.082
Only half? Where's your courage. Bunky?

417
00:58:52.165 --> 00:58:56.875
Courage is no match
for an unfriendly shoe. Countess.

418
00:58:57.885 --> 00:59:00.240
<i>- Un million.
- Bravo. Bunky.</i>

419
00:59:02.445 --> 00:59:06.358
<i>(croupier) Banco suivi.
Carte. s'il vous plaît.</i>

420
00:59:06.445 --> 00:59:09.164
A lucky night.

421
00:59:13.005 --> 00:59:14.996
<i>Carte.</i>

422
00:59:25.445 --> 00:59:28.084
The odds favor standing pat.

423
00:59:28.165 --> 00:59:30.156
If you play the odds.

424
00:59:31.845 --> 00:59:34.962
<i>(croupier) Neuf la banque.</i>

425
00:59:35.045 --> 00:59:37.195
<i>- (Bond) La main passe.
- La main passe.</i>

426
00:59:37.285 --> 00:59:40.436
<i>(Bond) Would you cash
these in for me. please?</i>

427
00:59:41.605 --> 00:59:44.403
Thank you. Excuse me.

428
01:00:02.205 --> 01:00:05.038
- Aperitif. please?
- Ouzo for me. please.

429
01:00:05.125 --> 01:00:07.593
Ouzo.

430
01:00:07.685 --> 01:00:10.074
And a whiskey.

431
01:00:11.045 --> 01:00:12.444
And to eat?

432
01:00:12.525 --> 01:00:17.280
<i>I'll have the Préveza prawns.
Savara salad. and bourdetto.</i>

433
01:00:17.365 --> 01:00:19.321
Excellent choice. I'll have the same.

434
01:00:19.405 --> 01:00:23.034
May I suggest a white Robola wine
from Cephalonia. my home place?

435
01:00:23.125 --> 01:00:26.800
If you'll forgive me. I find that
a little too scented for my palate.

436
01:00:26.885 --> 01:00:29.922
- I prefer the Theotaki Aspro.
- Theotaki.

437
01:00:32.125 --> 01:00:33.877
After our last meeting.

438
01:00:33.965 --> 01:00:38.800
I am asking myself why you want
to know about Locque. Columbo's man.

439
01:00:38.885 --> 01:00:43.675
Now. I know Columbo runs heroin to be
refined here before it is sent to England.

440
01:00:43.765 --> 01:00:49.397
So I think I see the answer.
You are from the British Narcotics Board.

441
01:00:50.005 --> 01:00:53.281
- Am I right?
- Go on.

442
01:00:54.005 --> 01:00:55.279
Hm.

443
01:00:55.365 --> 01:00:57.925
I wish you luck. my friend.

444
01:00:58.005 --> 01:01:00.997
But I must warn you.
Stopping Columbo will be difficult.

445
01:01:01.085 --> 01:01:04.441
He has important connections.
You cannot just arrest him.

446
01:01:04.525 --> 01:01:06.834
You must find a different way.

447
01:01:07.325 --> 01:01:12.843
You may have to kill him.
Does this discourage you?

448
01:01:14.885 --> 01:01:19.083
- Just tell me where he is.
- Over there. with the woman in blue.

449
01:01:22.685 --> 01:01:25.802
We ignore each other.
but I wanted you to see him.

450
01:01:25.885 --> 01:01:29.844
He is a secret partner in the casino here.
but we are perfectly safe.

451
01:01:29.925 --> 01:01:32.837
He will do nothing in his own place.

452
01:01:32.925 --> 01:01:35.075
And the Countess?

453
01:01:35.165 --> 01:01:39.522
Lisl? An Austrian. Expensive mistress.

454
01:01:39.605 --> 01:01:44.121
She sometimes shills for the house.
If she bets. it's with other people's money.

455
01:02:02.885 --> 01:02:05.035
<i>(rewinds tape)</i>

456
01:02:05.125 --> 01:02:08.117
<i>But I must warn you.
Stopping Columbo will be difficult.</i>

457
01:02:08.205 --> 01:02:11.515
<i>He has important connections.
You cannot just arrest him.</i>

458
01:02:11.605 --> 01:02:14.165
<i>You must find a different way.</i>

459
01:02:14.245 --> 01:02:20.115
<i>You may have to kill him.
Does this discourage you?</i>

460
01:02:21.405 --> 01:02:24.397
<i>Just tell me where he is.</i>

461
01:02:36.885 --> 01:02:40.241
You are a disgusting man.
How dare you talk to me like that?

462
01:02:40.325 --> 01:02:42.839
I will speak to you any way I please.

463
01:02:42.925 --> 01:02:46.838
Sit down. You're making
a spectacle of yourself.

464
01:02:48.365 --> 01:02:50.083
Get out!

465
01:02:50.165 --> 01:02:53.157
Nothing would please me more.

466
01:03:00.205 --> 01:03:03.197
- This may be an opportunity.
- This may be a trap.

467
01:03:03.285 --> 01:03:07.324
- If you play the odds.
- As you wish. Take my car.

468
01:03:07.405 --> 01:03:12.001
I'll play a little chemmy.
Ask the chauffeur to come back for me.

469
01:03:21.125 --> 01:03:22.843
Allow me.

470
01:03:22.925 --> 01:03:24.916
May I drive you home?

471
01:03:25.005 --> 01:03:27.519
No. thank you. I'll take a taxi.

472
01:03:27.605 --> 01:03:32.395
No courage? Seriously. you may
have a job finding one this time of night.

473
01:03:33.485 --> 01:03:36.283
Well. you look like a gentleman.

474
01:03:36.365 --> 01:03:38.356
Why not?

475
01:03:46.085 --> 01:03:48.235
I'm the Countess Lisl von Schlaf.

476
01:03:48.325 --> 01:03:50.122
My name is Bond.

477
01:03:50.205 --> 01:03:54.437
I'm a writer. I'm preparing a novel about
Greek smugglers. Do you know any?

478
01:03:54.525 --> 01:03:57.676
Smugglers?
How would I know any smugglers?

479
01:03:57.765 --> 01:04:03.840
I would have thought that a lady in your
position would get to know many things.

480
01:04:03.925 --> 01:04:07.122
- I'd really be most grateful.
- How grateful?

481
01:04:07.205 --> 01:04:08.399
Very.

482
01:04:09.245 --> 01:04:12.237
I adore grateful men.

483
01:04:40.645 --> 01:04:43.159
May I call you tomorrow. Countess?

484
01:04:43.245 --> 01:04:46.521
I'm a night person.
I've champagne and oysters in the fridge.

485
01:04:46.605 --> 01:04:48.755
Why not come in for a bite?

486
01:04:52.005 --> 01:04:54.997
I won't need you any more tonight.

487
01:05:20.565 --> 01:05:23.159
- Cheers.
- Bottoms up.

488
01:05:28.005 --> 01:05:29.723
Whoops!

489
01:05:29.805 --> 01:05:32.524
Me nightie's slipping.

490
01:05:32.605 --> 01:05:34.994
So's your accent. Countess.

491
01:05:36.285 --> 01:05:38.719
- Manchester?
- Close.

492
01:05:38.805 --> 01:05:41.114
Liverpool.

493
01:05:41.205 --> 01:05:46.120
It was a very amusing performance
between you and the owner of this.

494
01:05:46.205 --> 01:05:48.765
What exactly did
Columbo whisper to you?

495
01:05:48.845 --> 01:05:52.281
That you were a spy.
To find out more about you.

496
01:05:53.485 --> 01:05:56.204
And have you?

497
01:05:56.285 --> 01:05:58.879
Have I ever.

498
01:06:22.605 --> 01:06:26.723
When you're ready to leave.
you can take my car.

499
01:06:26.805 --> 01:06:32.038
Well. that sounds like a dismissal.
I was rather looking forward to breakfast.

500
01:06:39.045 --> 01:06:40.444
<i>(buggy approaches)</i>

501
01:06:47.205 --> 01:06:49.400
Oh. James!

502
01:07:09.925 --> 01:07:12.883
Lisl! Lisl. come back!

503
01:07:24.045 --> 01:07:25.717
<i>(screams)</i>

504
01:07:44.485 --> 01:07:46.043
Get in. Ugh!

505
01:07:58.005 --> 01:08:00.200
Goodbye. Countess.

506
01:08:04.845 --> 01:08:06.915
What...

507
01:08:44.885 --> 01:08:47.319
<i>(speaks Greek)</i>

508
01:08:47.405 --> 01:08:50.841
<i>- Now. what should I do with you?
- You can't just arrest him.</i>

509
01:08:50.925 --> 01:08:53.041
<i>You must find a different way.</i>

510
01:08:53.125 --> 01:08:57.721
<i>You may have to kill him.
Does this discourage you?</i>

511
01:08:58.885 --> 01:09:00.477
<i>Just tell me where he is.</i>

512
01:09:00.565 --> 01:09:05.081
I am here. Mr. Bond
of the British Secret Service.

513
01:09:05.165 --> 01:09:09.636
But I'll tell you.
it is Kristatos you want. not me.

514
01:09:10.365 --> 01:09:15.883
He told you about himself. He's the one
with the powerful connections.

515
01:09:15.965 --> 01:09:18.274
Locque works for him. not for me.

516
01:09:18.365 --> 01:09:24.076
I smuggle. yes. I smuggle gold.
diamonds. cigarettes. pistachio nuts.

517
01:09:24.165 --> 01:09:26.395
But no heroin.

518
01:09:26.485 --> 01:09:28.362
Sit down.

519
01:09:28.445 --> 01:09:32.802
That I leave to him. when he is
not too busy working for Russia.

520
01:09:32.885 --> 01:09:36.844
- Against my country and yours.
- My country awarded him a King's Medal.

521
01:09:36.925 --> 01:09:40.361
Yes. I know. but other people died for it.

522
01:09:40.445 --> 01:09:44.723
All through the fighting in Crete.
he was a double agent.

523
01:09:45.805 --> 01:09:48.603
King's Medal!

524
01:09:48.685 --> 01:09:53.805
I would laugh if my heart
was not so heavy about my poor Lisl.

525
01:09:55.565 --> 01:09:59.274
What does Kristatos gain
by setting you up?

526
01:09:59.365 --> 01:10:04.314
I know too much about him.
He wants me out of the way.

527
01:10:04.405 --> 01:10:09.957
By using a British agent
to do his dirty work for him.

528
01:10:10.045 --> 01:10:13.003
your government might
give him another medal.

529
01:10:13.085 --> 01:10:16.873
- Why should I believe you?
- I'll prove it to you tonight.

530
01:10:16.965 --> 01:10:21.561
We'll go together
to his warehouse in Albania.

531
01:10:21.925 --> 01:10:23.563
OK?

532
01:10:23.645 --> 01:10:27.240
If I don't report in by tomorrow morning.
not only will my people

533
01:10:27.325 --> 01:10:31.238
but the entire Greek police
be down on you like a load of bricks.

534
01:10:31.325 --> 01:10:36.524
Don't worry.
By tomorrow we'll be good friends.

535
01:10:38.045 --> 01:10:40.718
Let us drink to that.

536
01:10:40.805 --> 01:10:43.035
I'll wait till tomorrow.

537
01:10:54.445 --> 01:10:56.481
You may need this.

538
01:10:57.565 --> 01:10:59.556
I am a good judge of men.

539
01:10:59.645 --> 01:11:04.480
<i>Mr. Bond. you have
what the Greeks call thrassos.</i>

540
01:11:04.565 --> 01:11:06.078
Guts.

541
01:11:08.125 --> 01:11:10.593
So have you. Mr. Columbo.

542
01:11:17.845 --> 01:11:19.563
Cheers.

543
01:11:19.645 --> 01:11:21.556
<i>Yassou.</i>

544
01:11:58.045 --> 01:11:59.763
Locque!

545
01:12:28.005 --> 01:12:29.074
Phew!

546
01:12:58.725 --> 01:13:01.000
<i>Santos. sproxto.</i>

547
01:13:05.725 --> 01:13:06.874
Argh!

548
01:13:15.205 --> 01:13:16.604
Watch it.

549
01:13:22.005 --> 01:13:24.917
Santos. Nikos.

550
01:13:30.245 --> 01:13:31.758
<i>(creaking)</i>

551
01:13:31.845 --> 01:13:36.965
JIM diving equipment. for salvage work
at depths of more than 300 feet.

552
01:13:50.085 --> 01:13:52.360
Raw opium.

553
01:13:52.445 --> 01:13:55.278
An old smugglers' trick.
Kristatos knows them all.

554
01:14:01.605 --> 01:14:03.596
<i>(nut cracks)</i>

555
01:14:36.325 --> 01:14:39.044
Get your men out of here. Now!

556
01:14:45.005 --> 01:14:45.994
Argh!

557
01:16:12.205 --> 01:16:13.433
Argh!

558
01:16:38.085 --> 01:16:41.361
You left this with Ferrara. I believe.

559
01:16:58.485 --> 01:17:01.045
He had no head for heights.

560
01:18:26.765 --> 01:18:31.236
<i>- Where did the St. Georges sink?
- We can't be sure for certain.</i>

561
01:18:31.325 --> 01:18:36.080
We know it was in this vicinity. Your father
was using the temple as a front.

562
01:18:36.165 --> 01:18:41.364
<i>Kristatos killed your father because
he didn't want him to find the St. Georges.</i>

563
01:18:41.445 --> 01:18:43.834
Kristatos!

564
01:18:43.925 --> 01:18:45.916
How can I help?

565
01:18:46.005 --> 01:18:48.997
Where did your father
keep his records. his daily log?

566
01:18:49.085 --> 01:18:51.041
<i>(parrot) Daily log. Daily log.</i>

567
01:18:51.125 --> 01:18:55.721
Father and he were pals for 30 years.
He repeats everything.

568
01:18:58.485 --> 01:19:00.521
<i>(parrot) Give us a kiss.</i>

569
01:19:00.605 --> 01:19:02.561
- What's his name?
- Max.

570
01:19:02.645 --> 01:19:05.717
<i>- (parrot) Max.
- Thank you.</i>

571
01:19:07.085 --> 01:19:09.076
<i>(Max) Hello.</i>

572
01:19:12.485 --> 01:19:15.397
- It's all shorthand.
- He used a special kind.

573
01:19:15.485 --> 01:19:18.682
I was the only one who could decipher it.

574
01:19:21.605 --> 01:19:24.403
<i>He made several surveys in Neptune.</i>

575
01:19:24.485 --> 01:19:28.364
<i>- What's Neptune?
- Our two-man submarine.</i>

576
01:19:28.445 --> 01:19:31.915
According to this.
he saw a diving bell here.

577
01:19:32.005 --> 01:19:34.075
Diving bell?

578
01:19:34.165 --> 01:19:37.202
Oil exploration. Kristatos.

579
01:19:39.325 --> 01:19:43.841
Three days later. he sighted
a wreck in the same area.

580
01:19:43.925 --> 01:19:45.643
And?

581
01:19:45.725 --> 01:19:48.762
That was his last entry.
The day he was killed.

582
01:19:48.845 --> 01:19:52.679
Ah. Well. air would be
useless at this depth.

583
01:19:52.765 --> 01:19:55.723
We'd need a special mixture
of oxygen and helium.

584
01:19:55.805 --> 01:19:59.081
I have all the necessary
equipment aboard.

585
01:19:59.165 --> 01:20:01.884
The less people that know
about this. the better.

586
01:20:01.965 --> 01:20:05.514
I'll give the crew shore leave.
apart from the mate and two others.

587
01:20:05.605 --> 01:20:06.594
Let's go.

588
01:21:30.685 --> 01:21:35.839
that depth will gives us eight minutes.

589
01:21:35.925 --> 01:21:37.995
We're going to have to work fast.

590
01:21:38.085 --> 01:21:41.282
<i>Wouldn't the St. Georges crew
have destroyed the transmitter?</i>

591
01:21:41.365 --> 01:21:44.914
Only if they'd had the chance
to set the explosive timer.

592
01:22:12.365 --> 01:22:14.003
<i>(beeping)</i>

593
01:22:15.005 --> 01:22:17.803
We have a visitor below.

594
01:22:24.565 --> 01:22:29.241
<i>(Bond) Conserve your gas supply.
Speak only when necessary.</i>

595
01:23:11.005 --> 01:23:13.519
<i>(Melina screams)</i>

596
01:23:17.045 --> 01:23:20.401
<i>I hope he was dining alone.</i>

597
01:23:41.805 --> 01:23:43.238
<i>(Melina screams)</i>

598
01:23:43.325 --> 01:23:46.635
<i>- You'd better go back to the sub.
- No. no. I'm staying.</i>

599
01:23:57.405 --> 01:24:00.602
<i>(Bond) That should be
the command cabin.</i>

600
01:24:20.765 --> 01:24:22.756
<i>(Bond) Eureka.</i>

601
01:24:31.085 --> 01:24:34.794
<i>"Main destruct timer under lever
right of ATAC housing</i>

602
01:24:34.885 --> 01:24:40.357
<i>dualled by ring-mained circuit
through antihandling charger."</i>

603
01:24:40.445 --> 01:24:45.519
<i>The destruct timer's set at one minute.
For some reason. the lever wasn't pulled.</i>

604
01:24:51.365 --> 01:24:54.755
<i>The transmitter with a Thermite charge.</i>

605
01:24:57.885 --> 01:24:59.876
<i>(breathing)</i>

606
01:25:10.925 --> 01:25:12.961
<i>Hold these.</i>

607
01:25:13.045 --> 01:25:18.278
<i>"To bypass trembler switch.
cut wires in following procedure."</i>

608
01:25:19.765 --> 01:25:21.084
<i>Cutters.</i>

609
01:25:40.085 --> 01:25:41.564
<i>Screwdriver.</i>

610
01:25:47.165 --> 01:25:49.156
<i>(breathing)</i>

611
01:25:57.685 --> 01:26:00.279
<i>That's it. Let's get out of here.</i>

612
01:26:01.165 --> 01:26:03.076
<i>James!</i>

613
01:26:46.045 --> 01:26:48.036
<i>(ticking)</i>

614
01:27:01.725 --> 01:27:04.842
<i>- James. I won't make it.
- We both will.</i>

615
01:27:09.685 --> 01:27:13.075
<i>Get back to the sub fast. I'll stall him.</i>

616
01:27:25.845 --> 01:27:27.517
<i>(ticking)</i>

617
01:27:37.965 --> 01:27:39.956
<i>(ticking)</i>

618
01:29:48.045 --> 01:29:49.524
James!

619
01:30:25.765 --> 01:30:28.723
- Try and close the CO2.
- I'm trying.

620
01:31:53.285 --> 01:31:54.274
<i>(clunk)</i>

621
01:31:54.365 --> 01:31:58.040
Careful. James. It's 5000 years old.

622
01:32:35.245 --> 01:32:39.079
Thank you. Mr. Bond. You have saved us
the trouble of disarming it.

623
01:32:39.165 --> 01:32:41.474
Apostis. take that.

624
01:32:44.605 --> 01:32:48.917
- Where are the men I left on board?
- You will soon be joining them.

625
01:32:49.005 --> 01:32:52.918
Let the girl go. And I guarantee
we'll double whatever you're getting.

626
01:32:53.005 --> 01:32:58.921
Oh. I never go back on a deal.
It would be bad for my reputation.

627
01:33:15.325 --> 01:33:17.964
I will deliver it
and return with the money.

628
01:33:18.045 --> 01:33:23.358
The voice of the KGB. Our agreement was
to meet in a place designated by me.

629
01:33:24.005 --> 01:33:27.520
After they pay.
I will turn the transmitter over to them.

630
01:33:27.605 --> 01:33:32.395
- It must not go out of your sight. Apostis.
- Or mine. Kristatos. Where are we going?

631
01:33:32.485 --> 01:33:36.603
- We will take the ATAC to St. Cyrils.
- St. Cyrils?

632
01:33:36.685 --> 01:33:39.563
I'll arrange the pick-up.

633
01:33:44.965 --> 01:33:49.356
Ah. bind that wound.
We don't want any blood in the water.

634
01:33:49.445 --> 01:33:51.675
- Not yet.
- Murderer.

635
01:33:52.365 --> 01:33:56.563
You have shot your last bolt.
Miss Havelock.

636
01:33:59.605 --> 01:34:03.154
Leave the legs free.
They'll make appetizing bait.

637
01:34:12.645 --> 01:34:16.479
- I didn't think it would end like this.
- We're not dead yet.

638
01:34:42.045 --> 01:34:43.444
Hold tight.

639
01:35:07.685 --> 01:35:10.279
Turn around. We go again.

640
01:35:15.162 --> 01:35:17.551
Take a deep breath.

641
01:36:10.362 --> 01:36:13.513
Once again. Hurry.

642
01:36:37.602 --> 01:36:38.955
<i>(creaking)</i>

643
01:36:49.602 --> 01:36:50.796
Argh!

644
01:36:56.762 --> 01:36:58.992
<i>(shouts and screams)</i>

645
01:37:02.842 --> 01:37:04.161
Leave him.

646
01:37:06.802 --> 01:37:09.475
Turn. Run them down.

647
01:37:26.282 --> 01:37:28.398
<i>(Melina) Follow me.</i>

648
01:38:09.122 --> 01:38:10.999
Ah.

649
01:38:11.082 --> 01:38:14.791
The sharks have them. Make port.

650
01:38:35.162 --> 01:38:37.960
<i>- Thank you.
- (Max) Hello.</i>

651
01:38:40.922 --> 01:38:44.710
- Give us a kiss.
- Max. not now.

652
01:38:44.802 --> 01:38:47.441
Kristatos is still alive.

653
01:38:47.522 --> 01:38:51.151
He's probably on his way
to Moscow or Havana by now.

654
01:38:51.242 --> 01:38:54.712
- We'll never get him.
- Or the ATAC.

655
01:38:54.802 --> 01:38:57.760
ATAC to St. Cyrils. ATAC to St. Cyrils.

656
01:38:57.842 --> 01:38:59.833
<i>(Max squawks)</i>

657
01:39:02.642 --> 01:39:04.951
ATAC to St. Cyrils.

658
01:39:05.042 --> 01:39:08.432
<i>(band plays Greek wedding song)</i>

659
01:40:08.882 --> 01:40:11.237
Forgive me. Father. for I have sinned.

660
01:40:11.322 --> 01:40:14.553
That's putting it mildly. 007.

661
01:40:15.282 --> 01:40:17.876
Your signal sent Whitehall into shock.

662
01:40:17.962 --> 01:40:24.754
Do you know. so far we've managed
to locate 439 St. Cyrils in Greece?

663
01:40:24.842 --> 01:40:28.960
Heaven only knows to which one
Kristatos took the ATAC.

664
01:40:29.042 --> 01:40:32.239
I know a well-informed person
to contact about that. Q.

665
01:40:45.722 --> 01:40:49.476
<i>(Columbo) St. Cyrils. where
we used to hide from the Germans.</i>

666
01:40:49.562 --> 01:40:54.795
Only Kristatos would make an abandoned
monastery his personal retreat.

667
01:40:54.882 --> 01:41:00.275
My friend. I've been studying this place
for years for just such an occasion.

668
01:41:00.362 --> 01:41:05.914
We'll split here. The best approach will be
on the right face. away from the building.

669
01:41:06.002 --> 01:41:08.232
Then make towards the shed on the left.

670
01:41:08.322 --> 01:41:11.678
which houses the basket
and the electronic winch.

671
01:41:11.762 --> 01:41:14.481
It can be operated only from the shed.

672
01:41:15.162 --> 01:41:17.153
Good luck.

673
01:41:25.522 --> 01:41:28.912
<i>- We need more people.
- (Melina) James is counting on surprise.</i>

674
01:41:29.002 --> 01:41:32.711
- But we are only five men.
- And one woman.

675
01:42:22.242 --> 01:42:26.474
18...19...20...

676
01:42:27.562 --> 01:42:29.234
- 50 more.
- That's the pits!

677
01:42:29.322 --> 01:42:32.632
I'm supposed to be skating
in Oslo and Innsbruck.

678
01:42:32.722 --> 01:42:34.474
Why are we in this creepy place?

679
01:42:34.562 --> 01:42:38.794
Our plans are changed. We are going
to live in Cuba for a few months.

680
01:42:38.882 --> 01:42:40.076
Cuba?!

681
01:42:40.162 --> 01:42:43.359
You can skate privately.
I will be your audience.

682
01:42:43.442 --> 01:42:47.674
What a drag that'll be.
I wanna win the gold medal.

683
01:42:47.762 --> 01:42:49.434
We all want that.

684
01:42:49.522 --> 01:42:54.152
I know what you want.
But you're too old for me. I'm splitting.

685
01:42:55.002 --> 01:42:58.312
You have done this.
poisoned her against me!

686
01:42:58.402 --> 01:43:00.791
Don't blow your top. Ari. Leave her alone.

687
01:43:00.882 --> 01:43:06.240
I will deal with you. Jacoba Brink.
as I deal with everyone who betrays me.

688
01:43:15.002 --> 01:43:18.995
Bibi. you're so young.

689
01:43:20.362 --> 01:43:24.435
- You must have a sponsor.
- I'll find another one.

690
01:43:24.522 --> 01:43:29.277
Go outside and check the guards. Let me
know as soon as the helicopter arrives.

691
01:45:57.642 --> 01:45:59.633
<i>(Bond grunts)</i>

692
01:48:18.882 --> 01:48:20.873
<i>(man screams)</i>

693
01:48:24.522 --> 01:48:26.513
<i>(Melina) James!</i>

694
01:48:29.882 --> 01:48:32.715
Apostis. One of Kristatos' killers.

695
01:50:04.802 --> 01:50:07.316
<i>(winch winds)</i>

696
01:51:09.082 --> 01:51:12.119
<i>- (man groans)
- Shut him up!</i>

697
01:51:16.042 --> 01:51:18.237
Get the door.

698
01:51:27.202 --> 01:51:30.239
Hurry. unless you want me
to go without you.

699
01:51:30.322 --> 01:51:33.758
You know I will never leave you.

700
01:51:36.282 --> 01:51:38.591
Your general is late.

701
01:51:38.682 --> 01:51:41.150
Only bad weather would delay him.

702
01:51:54.722 --> 01:51:58.761
<i>(Bond) Cover the windows. Let's go.</i>

703
01:51:58.842 --> 01:52:01.436
He's all right. leave him.

704
01:52:08.362 --> 01:52:09.954
He's all right.

705
01:52:10.042 --> 01:52:11.794
Back.

706
01:52:14.722 --> 01:52:16.713
<i>- (man groans)
- Sh!</i>

707
01:52:19.882 --> 01:52:22.237
OK. Let's go.

708
01:52:22.322 --> 01:52:24.995
I'll be with you.

709
01:52:25.082 --> 01:52:25.958
Sorry.

710
01:52:37.682 --> 01:52:40.321
Cover the door!

711
01:52:40.402 --> 01:52:42.996
Where's Kristatos? Keep your voice down.

712
01:52:43.082 --> 01:52:46.518
We are leaving him.
He must not know until we are gone.

713
01:52:46.602 --> 01:52:50.595
<i>- We'll help you if you help us.
- Ja. mein Herr Bond. Ja.</i>

714
01:52:50.682 --> 01:52:52.479
Come.

715
01:53:02.522 --> 01:53:06.151
- Where are the guards?
- That way.

716
01:53:39.842 --> 01:53:41.639
Hey.

717
01:53:55.442 --> 01:53:57.034
Move.

718
01:54:00.442 --> 01:54:03.832
- Where's Kristatos?
- The other side of the courtyard.

719
01:54:03.922 --> 01:54:06.516
You'd better stay here.

720
01:54:14.402 --> 01:54:16.870
Where's Brink?
What have you done to her?

721
01:54:16.962 --> 01:54:20.272
- Go back to your room.
- You can go to hell!

722
01:54:51.162 --> 01:54:53.357
Drop it.

723
01:55:00.322 --> 01:55:02.677
<i>(grunting)</i>

724
01:56:12.162 --> 01:56:15.120
- Where's Kristatos?
- He left with the ATAC.

725
01:56:25.642 --> 01:56:28.952
You're going to pay for it.

726
01:56:42.482 --> 01:56:47.158
No. Melina. That's not the answer.
We'll turn him over to the Greek police.

727
01:56:47.242 --> 01:56:49.198
Out of my way. James.

728
01:56:49.882 --> 01:56:54.478
All right. But be prepared
to dig those two graves.

729
01:57:11.322 --> 01:57:13.313
<i>Nyet!</i>

730
01:57:30.202 --> 01:57:35.276
That's détente. comrade.
You don't have it. I don't have it.

731
01:57:37.402 --> 01:57:39.199
<i>(laughs)</i>

732
01:58:06.082 --> 01:58:09.870
Well. seems as though
Bibi has a new sponsor.

733
01:58:19.642 --> 01:58:23.715
- Well. how's it going?
- I patched through a line to the satellite.

734
01:58:23.802 --> 01:58:26.316
- We can try Bond now.
- Good.

735
01:58:26.402 --> 01:58:29.678
- Are you through to Number 10?
- Standing by. sir.

736
01:58:33.442 --> 01:58:36.639
You know what I'd like?

737
01:58:36.722 --> 01:58:38.792
I can't imagine.

738
01:58:38.882 --> 01:58:41.032
A moonlight swim.

739
01:58:41.842 --> 01:58:43.434
<i>(beeping)</i>

740
01:58:45.002 --> 01:58:47.835
<i>(Q) 007. are you there?</i>

741
01:58:51.442 --> 01:58:53.239
<i>Bond?</i>

742
01:58:53.802 --> 01:58:55.599
<i>Bond?</i>

743
01:58:56.602 --> 01:59:00.481
<i>Bond. are you there? Bond!</i>

744
01:59:00.562 --> 01:59:02.712
For your eyes only. darling.

745
01:59:02.802 --> 01:59:05.362
<i>(Max squawks)</i>

746
01:59:05.442 --> 01:59:07.114
<i>(Q) Bond? Bond?</i>

747
01:59:07.202 --> 01:59:08.317
Bond. Bond.

748
01:59:08.402 --> 01:59:10.870
- He's there.
- Patch in the prime minister.

749
01:59:12.522 --> 01:59:14.558
<i>(phone rings)</i>

750
01:59:14.642 --> 01:59:17.236
I'll get it. Denis.

751
01:59:19.522 --> 01:59:22.639
- Hello?
- Mr. Bond on the line. Prime Minister.

752
01:59:22.722 --> 01:59:24.758
Ah. Mr. Bond.

753
01:59:25.602 --> 01:59:29.356
I wanted to call you personally
to say how pleased we all are

754
01:59:29.442 --> 01:59:32.434
that your mission was a success.
Thank you.

755
01:59:32.522 --> 01:59:35.559
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Don't thank me. Mr. Bond.

756
01:59:35.642 --> 01:59:40.557
Your courage and resourcefulness
are a credit to the nation.

757
01:59:40.642 --> 01:59:42.758
Denis and I look forward to meeting you.

758
01:59:42.842 --> 01:59:45.515
Meanwhile. if there
is anything I can do for you...

759
01:59:45.602 --> 01:59:50.722
- Give us a kiss. Give us a kiss.
- Well. really. Mr. Bond.

760
01:59:50.802 --> 01:59:54.636
<i>- I think we're having trouble with the line.
- (Max) Give us a kiss.</i>

761
01:59:54.722 --> 01:59:58.510
- You idiot. Get on to him.
- 007.

762
01:59:58.602 --> 02:00:01.036
<i>- (Max laughs)
- 007!</i>

763
02:00:01.122 --> 02:00:03.590
Bond. have you gone mad?
What's going on?

764
02:00:03.682 --> 02:00:06.150
<i>- Bond? Bond! Bond!
- (Max laughs)</i>

765
02:00:07.042 --> 02:00:13.356
<i># For your eyes only
can see me through the night</i>

766
02:00:15.202 --> 02:00:21.198
<i># For your eyes only I never need to hide</i>

767
02:00:23.522 --> 02:00:29.154
<i># You can see so much in me.
so much in me that's new</i>

768
02:00:31.522 --> 02:00:38.280
<i># I never felt until I looked at you</i>

769
02:00:38.362 --> 02:00:42.560
<i># For your eyes only</i>

770
02:00:42.642 --> 02:00:45.076
<i># Only for you</i>

771
02:00:45.162 --> 02:00:49.838
<i># You'll see what no one else can see
and now I'm breaking free</i>

772
02:00:49.922 --> 02:00:53.437
<i># For your eyes only</i>

773
02:00:53.522 --> 02:00:56.161
<i># Only for you</i>

774
02:00:56.242 --> 02:00:58.915
<i># The love I know you need in me</i>

775
02:00:59.002 --> 02:01:01.835
<i># The fantasy you've freed in me</i>

776
02:01:01.922 --> 02:01:05.710
<i># Only for you</i>

777
02:01:05.922 --> 02:01:09.631
<i># Only for you</i>

778
02:01:17.922 --> 02:01:23.918
<i># For your eyes only.
the nights are never cold</i>

779
02:01:26.122 --> 02:01:32.118
<i># You really know me.
that's all I need to know</i>

780
02:01:34.482 --> 02:01:40.478
<i># Maybe I'm an open book
because I know you're mine</i>

781
02:01:42.442 --> 02:01:49.200
<i># But you don't need
to read between the lines</i>

782
02:01:49.282 --> 02:01:53.514
<i># For your eyes only</i>

783
02:01:53.602 --> 02:01:56.036
<i># Only for you</i>

784
02:01:56.122 --> 02:02:00.832
<i># You'll see what no one else can see
and now I'm breaking free</i>

785
02:02:00.922 --> 02:02:04.392
<i># For your eyes only</i>

786
02:02:04.482 --> 02:02:07.076
<i># Only for you</i>

787
02:02:07.162 --> 02:02:09.915
<i># The passions that collide in me</i>

788
02:02:10.002 --> 02:02:12.721
<i># The wild abandoned side of me</i>

789
02:02:12.802 --> 02:02:16.351
<i># Only for you</i>

790
02:02:16.442 --> 02:02:21.641
<i># For your eyes only</i>
